Chapter:1

Note: Host uses MAC adderess to communicate inside the network,And IP address to
communicate over a remote network.

Servers: Computers with software that enable them to provide infromation, like email or web pages
to other end devices on the network.

Clinets: Computer with software installed that enable them to request and display the information obtained from server.

Peer-to-Peer: when computer function as clinets and servers on the same network.


Converged Networks: Networks that are capable of delivering data, voice and video between devices over the same network.

intranet: is a LAN or WAN network that's private for an orginization members only.
OSI Model: Well-defined Model for communication systems. OSI Model is a view of how one system sould
communicate with other systems using various Protocols.

Protocals: A set of defined rules.
















